news.headline: Durable Goods Orders Down 9.3% In June, Less Than Expected
news.summary: New orders for manufactured durable goods fell 9.3% to $311.85 in June, the largest monthly decline since 2020.

news.headline: Recession Risk In Autumn 2025 Rising With Tariff Uncertainty
news.summary: There are plenty of small negatives which don't add up to a recession. Recession risk comes from the continued back-and-forth from the White House about what tariffs will be. Read more here.

news.headline: Liquidity Drain Is Coming, And Markets May Soon Feel It
news.summary: $500B liquidity drain looms as the Treasury refills the TGA, impacting markets. Watch SOFR rates and Fed facilities for early signs. Click for more.
